{
  "_comment": [
    "Parity fixture for scripts/diff-connectors.ts — ONE file, fed to BOTH the Rust",
    "`magnis-google` binary and the `google-ts` twin via GOOGLE_FIXTURE_FILE.",
    "Every entry targets a branch in the Rust oracle (the incumbent the host talks to):",
    "  gmail.rs   gmail_message_to_mail_message / parse_email_address(es) / get_header",
    "             / parse_rfc2822_date / internal_date_to_datetime / flatten_mail_payload",
    "  mime.rs    extract_body_content / collect_attachments / decode_base64url",
    "  calendar.rs gcal_event_to_calendar_event / resolve_datetime",
    "  contacts.rs gpeople_person_to_contact / pick_primary / stable_contact_id",
    "NOTE deliberately NO event without start/end and NO contact needing Utc::now():",
    "calendar.rs:255 `_ => Ok((Utc::now(), false))` is wall-clock and can never be",
    "diffed across two processes. That branch is called out in the report instead."
  ],

